    <p class="gd-lede">Iceland's Tröllaskagi (Troll) Peninsula is one of the few places on earth where you can drop from an Arctic summit and ski a clean, unbroken line all the way to the ocean. This chapter maps the terrain in detail — the eleven zones, the range of lines, how much you ski in a day and what makes it unlike anywhere else. It sits within the wider story of heliskiing in <a href="/iceland">Iceland</a>.</p>
